<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>ant’s pants • have ants in one’s pants</xh5><p> <i>ant’s pants</i>—(Austral. sl.) the height of fashion; the ultimate in novelty or style: You always think it’s the <u>ant’s pants</u>, and then something better comes along.</p><p> <i>have ants in one’s pants</i>—<i>(coll.)</i> 1. fidget constantly because of extreme nervousness: Why can’t you stand still, do you <u>have ants in your pants</u>? 2. be impatient or restless: The boss <u>has ants in his pants</u> and wants us to have it all ready for him on Tuesday morning.</p> </entry>
